  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

records.addlTxt: Defendant Alexandria J Walton in court.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.
Correction as to 8-20-2015 entry:  the domestic violence surcharge is not applicable to this case.

Defendant Alexandria J Walton in court with attorney Andrew R Rider.  Abbey Marie DeSiato appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Upon oral motion of the state, count of Child Abuse, Intentionally Cause Harm is amended to 2 counts of Battery( hereafter referenced as COUNT 1 AND COUNT 3), a class A misdemeanor, 940.19(1) and count of Neglecting a Child is amended to Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, 947.01(1).
AS to al three counts:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
Sentencing proceeded.    Statements by the state and defense.  Defendant stands silent.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.
As to counts 1 and 3(Battery):   Defendant sentenced to serve 6 months each count consecutive in the House of Correction.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 months concurrent.
*
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction, consecutive, each count.  This time is stayed pending a review on 12-11-2015 at 1:15pm.
-Mental Health Evaluation and take ALL prescribed medication, and/or any treatment deemed appropriate.        
-Successfully complete Anger Management, and continued programming.
-Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment including random urine screens.
-Maintain absolute sobriety.
-Successfully complete any other counseling and/or treatment deemed appropriate. Parenting classes.
-No contact with victim, UNLESS the victim requests contact, and then only after the agent or court or Children's Court has approved contact.
-Defendant to pay all (counts 1,2,3) applicable costs and surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.
-Defendant to pay all supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.
-Obtain and maintain employment.
-No firearms; weapons.
-Restitution is set at 0.
AS to count 2(DISORDERLY CONDUCT):  The court sentences the defendant to serve 90 days in the House of Correction but STAYS that sentence until the review date on 12-11-2015.  All costs, assessments and surcharges to be paid during probation in counts 1 and 3.
Received and filed:  Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.  Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order and due to this DV conviction she may never possess firearms or ammunition.  Case adjourned to Branch 38.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for December 11, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
